    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-02-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="970"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d970">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Woodford</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-02-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 17, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 146.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have this moment received a note from the
                    Spanish minister of foreign affairs, dated this 17th day of February, instant,
                    informing me that Her Majesty the Queen Regent has signed a decree nominating
                    Don Luis Polo de Bernabé to be envoy extraordinary and minister plenipotentiary
                    of Spain in the Republic of the United States. Señor Polo de Bernabé was at the
                    time of his appointment chief of the section or bureau of commerce of the
                    foreign office of Spain.</p>
                <pb facs="1111" n="1015" xml:id="pg_1015"/>
                <p>I telegraph you as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>, <hi rend="italic">February 17,
                                1898.</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Secretary <hi rend="smallcaps">Sherman</hi>, <hi
                                rend="italic">Washington:</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p>Have just received official communication from Spanish minister of
                            foreign affairs that the Queen Regent has to-day signed decree
                            appointing Señor Polo de Bernabé minister from Spain to the United
                            States.</p>
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodford.</hi>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stewart L. Woodford.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
